The paper also deals with cooperative vehicular systems, which can be considered as cyber-physical systems, leading to the possibility of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a likely category. The paper proposes a timed distributed protocol, which can be considered as a distributed computing problem, leading to the possibility of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as a likely category. The paper also proposes a deterministic solution, which can be considered as an artificial intelligence problem, leading to the possibility of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a likely category. Finally, the paper deals with communication failures, which can be considered as a security and privacy problem, leading to the possibility of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as a likely category.
